  "elapsed_s": 11.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "--but the only-- the only restrictions that were made were that in Hebrew Gymnasium, which was my alma mater, the educational-- the new educational authorities dictated to the college that Hebrew is prohibited because Hebrew was-- was the expression of Zionist a-- a [NON-ENGLISH] point of view.",
      "word_count": 47
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And Hebrew had to be replaced with Yiddish.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And Yiddish was the-- the accepted common tongue of the-- the-- the-- the Russian [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They had their own Yiddish written in-- in a-- in-- in a way where Hebrew words were written with-- with Yiddish spellings.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So if you take today a book published by the [NON-ENGLISH] in-- of-- from-- from-- in-- from Russia, you find it very hard to read it without just raising an eyebrow every so often about the-- the-- the-- the-- the-- the-- for the-- for the trained eye to accept it.",
      "word_count": 50
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But that's how it was.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But that was a dictate of a political nature.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "How it translated itself in terms of the self-govern-- governing bodies of the community of the kehilla, I'm not in a situation to tell you.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But the-- the-- but if-- if that is any indication at all, I think it is saying a great deal because it goes to the very core about some of the basic elements of the transformation as far as Jewish lives are concerned.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The word 'Zionism' became suddenly traif.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was-- it was unmentionable, and-- and-- and-- and that was it.",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
